<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<style>
body {
  background-color: yellow;
}

@media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  body {
    background-color: lightblue;
  }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>The @media Rule</h1>

<p>Resize the browser window. When the width of this document is 600 pixels or less, the background-color is "lightblue", otherwise it is "yellow".</p>

</body>
</html>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
p {
  background-color: yellow;  
}

p.ex1 {
  min-height: 100px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>The min-height Property</h1>

<h2>min-height: none (default):</h2>
<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam semper diam at erat pulvinar, at pulvinar felis blandit...</p>

<h2>min-height: 200px:</h2>
<p class="ex1">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam semper diam at erat pulvinar, at pulvinar felis blandit...</p>

</body>
</html>
